## Recommended Workflow

### 1. Understand current state first

```
dashboard_state           →  see all apps, their statuses, active overrides
screenshot                →  confirm the visible UI
screenshot { labels: true } → labeled screenshot showing interactive elements
accessibility_snapshot    →  get page structure as text
console_logs              →  check for errors
network_log               →  verify API calls
```

### 2. Set up overrides for local development

```
override_app { action: "set", appName: "@cnic/main", url: "http://localhost:9100/app.js" }
```

After setting an override, the extension panel will auto-sync within ~3 seconds.

### 3. Verify changes are effective

```
dashboard_state  →  confirm overrideUrl shows your localhost URL
screenshot       →  confirm the UI reflects your local code
```

### 4. Complex interactions with Playwright

```
playwright_execute { code: "await page.click('button[type=submit]')" }
playwright_execute { code: "state.formData = await page.inputValue('#email')" }
playwright_execute { code: "await page.fill('#name', 'Test User')" }
```

Use `playwright_execute` for: Playwright locators, form filling, multi-step flows, assertions.
Use `execute` for: quick JS evaluation in page context, reading DOM values, calling page APIs.

### 5. Debug with console and network logs

```
console_logs { level: "error" }          →  filter errors only
console_logs { search: "API" }           →  find API-related logs
network_log { status_filter: "error" }   →  find failed requests
network_log { url_filter: "api.example" } →  filter by URL
network_detail { requestId: "R1.2" }     →  get full headers + request/response body
network_detail { requestId: "R1.2", include: "response_body", max_body_size: 5000 }
```

### 6. Track page changes with snapshot diff

```
accessibility_snapshot                    →  first call caches baseline
accessibility_snapshot                    →  second call shows diff
accessibility_snapshot { search: "button" } →  search for specific elements
accessibility_snapshot { diff: false }    →  force full snapshot (no diff)
```

### 7. Debug JavaScript with breakpoints

```
debugger { action: "enable" }
debugger { action: "list_scripts", search: "app.js" }
debugger { action: "set_breakpoint", file: "app.js", line: 42 }
debugger { action: "set_breakpoint", file: "utils.js", line: 10, condition: "x > 5" }
debugger { action: "resume" }
debugger { action: "step_over" }
debugger { action: "evaluate", expression: "localVar" }
debugger { action: "inspect_variables" }
debugger { action: "pause_on_exceptions", state: "uncaught" }
```

### 8. Inspect CSS styles

```
css_inspect { selector: "#header" }
css_inspect { selector: ".btn-primary", properties: "color,background-color,font-size" }
```

### 9. Manage multiple Playwright sessions

```
session_manager { action: "create", sessionId: "feature-test" }
session_manager { action: "list" }
session_manager { action: "switch", sessionId: "feature-test" }
session_manager { action: "remove", sessionId: "feature-test" }
session_manager { action: "remove_all" }
```

### 10. Manage browser storage

```
storage { action: "get_cookies" }                               →  list all cookies
storage { action: "set_cookie", name: "debug", value: "1" }   →  set a cookie
storage { action: "get_local_storage" }                        →  list all localStorage
storage { action: "get_local_storage", key: "theme" }          →  get specific key
storage { action: "set_local_storage", key: "theme", value: "dark" }
storage { action: "clear_storage", storage_types: "local_storage" }
storage { action: "get_storage_usage" }                        →  check quota/usage
```

### 11. Monitor performance

```
performance { action: "get_metrics" }           →  runtime metrics (heap, nodes, timing)
performance { action: "get_web_vitals" }        →  LCP, CLS, INP, FCP, TTFB with grading
performance { action: "get_memory" }            →  JS heap, DOM nodes, listeners
performance { action: "get_resource_timing" }   →  slowest resources by duration
performance { action: "get_resource_timing", type_filter: "fetch", count: 10 }
```

### 12. Edit page sources live

```
editor { action: "list_sources", search: "app" }    →  find loaded scripts
editor { action: "get_source", scriptId: "123", line_start: 1, line_end: 50 }
editor { action: "edit_source", scriptId: "123", content: "..." }   →  hot-reload
editor { action: "search_source", search: "TODO" }  →  search across all scripts
editor { action: "list_stylesheets" }                →  find CSS sheets
editor { action: "get_stylesheet", styleSheetId: "0" }
editor { action: "edit_stylesheet", styleSheetId: "0", content: "body { color: red; }" }
```

### 13. Intercept network requests

```
network_intercept { action: "enable" }
network_intercept { action: "add_rule", url_pattern: "/api/users", mock_status: 200, mock_body: "[{\"id\":1}]" }
network_intercept { action: "add_rule", url_pattern: "/ads/", block: true }
network_intercept { action: "list_rules" }
network_intercept { action: "remove_rule", rule_id: "rule_1" }
network_intercept { action: "disable" }
```

### 14. Emulate devices and conditions

```
emulation { action: "set_device", width: 375, height: 812, device_scale_factor: 3, mobile: true }
emulation { action: "set_network_conditions", preset: "slow-3g" }
emulation { action: "set_geolocation", latitude: 37.7749, longitude: -122.4194 }
emulation { action: "set_timezone", timezone_id: "America/New_York" }
emulation { action: "set_media", features: "prefers-color-scheme:dark" }
emulation { action: "clear_all" }
```

### 15. Get page content

```
page_content { action: "get_html" }                    →  clean HTML (no scripts/styles)
page_content { action: "get_html", selector: "#main" } →  scoped to element
page_content { action: "get_text" }                    →  plain text content
page_content { action: "get_metadata" }                →  title, meta, OG tags, counts
page_content { action: "search_dom", search: "error" } →  find elements by text/attr
```

### 16. Make code changes, then verify

```
ensure_fresh_render  →  reload with fresh cache after code changes
dashboard_state      →  re-confirm state
screenshot           →  visual check
```

### 17. Cleanup when done

```
override_app { action: "remove", appName: "@cnic/main" }
   — or —
override_app { action: "reset_all" }    ← removes ALL overrides at once
```

